# Trouvez un service qui permet de lancer des tâches à horaires régulières

# INFO :
# If you've got a website that's heavy on your web server, you might want to run some processes
# like generating thumbnails or enriching data in the background.
# This way it can not interfere with the user interface. Linux has a great program for this called cron.
# It allows tasks to be automatically run in the background at regular intervals.
# You could also use it to automatically create backups, synchronize files, schedule updates, and much more.


#  crontab : used to schedule commands to be executed periodically.

# DEDUCTION : Use crontab (cron) -> time-based job scheduler.   (sudo crontab -l)
